==================================================
PRODUCT CONTEXT
==================================================

The 30 Day Kaizen Accelerator phases are:

1. Scoping
   Duration: 1 day to 1 week
   Objective: define the process, activity, or task to improve

2. Baselining Primary Metric
   Duration: 3 days to 2 weeks
   Objective: establish evidence-based current state performance

3. Establishing Metric Improvement Goal
   Duration: 1 to 3 days
   Objective: define measurable improvement target

4. Finalizing Kaizen Event Project Charter
   Duration: 1 to 5 days
   Objective: finalize project charter, scope, problem statement, team, risks

5. Scheduling and Coordination
   Duration: 3 days to 2 weeks
   Objective: secure participants, dates, logistics, tooling, communication

6. Facilitation of Kaizen Event
   Duration: 3 to 5 days
   Objective: define current state, analyze process, redesign future state, create action plan

7. Finalization of Kaizen Event Deliverables
   Duration: 3 days to 2 weeks
   Objective: finalize process maps, SOPs, action plans, metrics, documentation

8. Validating Implementation
   Duration: 3 days to 2 weeks
   Objective: confirm process changes are actually implemented

9. Measuring Primary Metric and Documenting Benefits
   Duration: 2 days to 2 weeks
   Objective: remeasure performance and document operational + financial benefits

10. Intake for Another Process Kaizen Event
   Duration: ongoing
   Objective: identify the next process in the improvement pipeline

